<br>
Therianthrope is a part-animal human. Their are real therianthropes, though none/few can perform a physical shift.<br>
<br>
They get Dual wield, low cap double attack, leather armor. Blunts, HtH, and slashing (claw weapons only). They get Animal Form skills. <br>
<br>
Like at 9 they can get snake form, which gives them a weak poison proc, and maybe 3% haste to attacks. <br>
<br>
At 15 maybe they can get Cougar Form, 8% haste, +7str +7sta +10agi.<br>
<br>
Then at 21 maybe bear form. 6% slow, +20str +20 sta +15atk<br>
<br>
Then at 29 or 30, perhaps a tiger form. 20% haste, +5str +10sta +5atk <br>
<br>
And it just gets better from there!<br>
<br>
As far as an archer. I want a leather based class, high off/def caps. Innate +atk bonus with archery. No dual wield, no double attack on melee, low cap on melee skills (75 - 100).<br>
<br>
However archery is thier main form of fighting. Getting Double attack for archery (15?), Archery crits starting at 20 or 25, double damage shots at 45, a trueshot type skill that we get at 45 or so but lasts say, a full minute and is usable once a day. <br>
<br>
IE an entirely archery based class with low melee skills. Would be very group dependant, but would contribute a lot. However this would require the fixing of some of the more prevelent archery bugs in game now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulukasmoss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LukasmosS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/23/02 8:24:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28564.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WEll!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> A Therianthrope, ...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
